name: Respect for Our Elders Day
text: [§8-9]  Respect for Our Elders Day.  The third Sunday of October shall be known and recognized as "Respect for Our Elders Day" during which our elders may be honored with appropriate displays, celebrations, and ceremonies.  Respect for Our Elders Day shall not be taken as a state holiday. [L 1986, c 15, §1]
